quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  112,1,"Say: “He is Allah, the One<sup>1</sup>;","[1] He is Alone, without a partner, indivisible and distinct from all else. The only true deity, unique in His essence, attributes, and actions."
  112,2,"Allah, the Eternal Refuge<sup>2</sup>.","[2] He is absolute, perfect, complete, self-sufficient; the one eternally and constantly required and sought; all existence depend upon Him; all matters ultimately return to Him."
  112,3,"He neither begets nor is He begotten,",""
  112,4,"and there is none comparable to Him.”<sup>3</sup>","[3] The Prophet (ﷺ) says that reading this surah (surat al-Ikhlās) equals reading one third of the Qur’an. [Al-Bukhāri and Muslim]"
  113,1,"Say, “I seek refuge with the Lord of the daybreak,",""
  113,2,"from the harm of all what He has created;",""
  113,3,"from the harm of darkening [night] when it spreads around,",""
  113,4,"from the harm of the sorceresses<sup>1</sup> who blow on knots,","[1] i.e., magicians."
  113,5,"and from the harm of the envier when he envies.""",""
  114,1,"Say, “I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind,",""
  114,2,"the Sovereign of mankind<sup>1</sup>,","[1] i.e., the King of mankind."
  114,3,"the God of mankind,",""
  114,4,"from the harm of the lurking whisperer<sup>2</sup>,","[2] Which disappears when one remembers Allah."
  114,5,"who whispers into the hearts of mankind,",""
  114,6,"from among jinn and mankind<sup>3</sup>.”","[3] Evil prompters and whisperers can be from jinn or from men."
